name: Upton Court Park Orchard
short_description: Heritage fruit with a view of Windsor Castle.
description: Established apple and pear trees located near the southern boundary, open for public picking.

name: Burnham Beeches Sweet Chestnuts
description: Mature sweet chestnut trees are abundant throughout this ancient woodland on the Slough fringe.

name: Jubilee River Wild Garlic
description: Shaded banks along the Jubilee River relief channel are becoming a hotspot for wild garlic in spring.

name: Incredible Edible Slough - High St
short_description: Urban planters in the town centre.
description: Community raised beds featuring kale, chives, and seasonal kitchen herbs outside the library.

name: Cippenham Moat Blackberries
description: The wild scrub surrounding this ancient scheduled monument is excellent for blackberry picking.

name: Black Park Elder
description: Large elder bushes are scattered throughout the parkland and near the lake.

name: Salt Hill Park Walnuts
description: Mature walnut trees can be found in the quieter corners of this Victorian park.

name: Grand Union Canal Sloes
description: The towpath of the Grand Union Canal Slough Arm is lined with blackthorn bushes.

name: Herschel Park Rosehips
short_description: Wild berries in a nature reserve.
description: Wild rose bushes providing rosehips line the trails around the lake and nature area.

name: Britwell Incredible Edible Planters
description: Street-side beds with accessible strawberries and culinary herbs for locals.

name: Stoke Poges Lane Hazelnuts
description: Hazel trees are found in the older hedgerows along the lanes heading toward Stoke Poges.

name: Slough Trading Estate Apples
description: Feral apple trees grow in several green buffers and abandoned verges within the estate.

name: Colne Valley Wild Mint
description: Damp drainage dykes and riverbanks along the Colne Valley trail are rich with watermint.

name: Haymill Valley Sloes
description: The blackthorn scrub in this local nature reserve provides a good crop of sloes.

name: Langley Park Samphire (Marsh Alternative)
description: Wild celery and other damp-loving edible greens can be found in the marshy areas near the park's watercourses.
